Using the .format() Method - Exercise #5
Obtain the following output:

"Company B expects their next year's sales of Q4 to remain the same."

while referring to the following three lists:

companies = ['Company A', 'Company B']
quarter = [1, 2, 3, 4]
sales_performance_prediction = ['increase', 'decrease', 'remain the same'] 




companies = ['Company A', 'Company B']
quarter = [1, 2, 3, 4]
sales_performance_prediction = ['increase', 'decrease', 'remain the same'] 
print("{comp} expects their next year's sales of Q{quat} to {sal}.".format(comp=companies[1],quat=quarter[3],sal=sales_performance_prediction[2]))
